[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-20T21:15:39+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of the Sonos Android app playing a song on the Era 300 speaker.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/w3i6K89y7feRdVK_6SQQcIKknDA=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73533479/DSCF0495.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Chris Welch / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"mH3gha\">If you want the old Sonos app back, it\u2019s not coming. In a Reddit AMA response posted Tuesday, Sonos CEO Spence <a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/sonos/comments/1ew62yv/august_office_hours_w_keithfromsonos/lj3jwb8/\">says that</a> he was hopeful \u201cuntil very recently\u201d that the company could rerelease the app, confirming <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/14/24220421/sonos-s2-app-relaunch\">a report from <em>The Verge</em></a> that the company was considering doing so. But after testing that option, rereleasing the old app would apparently make things worse, Spence says.</p>\n<p id=\"8QwWI1\">Since the new app was released on May 7th, Sp", "id": 1033615, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/20/24224754/sonos-ceo-old-s2-app-re-release-cant-be", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Sonos CEO says the old app can\u2019t be rereleased", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-20T21:14:26+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An iPhone and set of AirPods wirelessly charging on the Nomad Base One Max MagSafe three-in-one charger.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/19PTEoSQdcitF5VbiPhq